<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">What type network card I’ve installed?</span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> pciconf</span> <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">-lv </span>| <span style="font-weight: bold;">grep</span> <span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">-B3</span> <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">network</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">bge0@pci0:2:0:0:    class=0x020000 card=0x16b414e4 chip=0x16b414e4 rev=0x10 hdr=0x00</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">    vendor     = 'Broadcom Limited'</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">    device     = 'NetXtreme BCM57765 Gigabit Ethernet PCIe'</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">    class      = network</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">none2@pci0:3:0:0:    class=0x028000 card=0x00f5106b chip=0x433114e4 rev=0x02 hdr=0x00</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">    vendor     = 'Broadcom Limited'</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">    device     = 'BCM4331 802.11a/b/g/n'</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">    class      = network</span></div><div>--------------------------------------------------------------------</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">What is the network card interface name in the system?</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># The during the boot the system will detect your card and you can find</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># out the interface name assigned by the FreeBSD :</span></div><div>=&gt; <span style="font-weight: bold;">cat</span> <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> /var/run/</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 150, 255);">dmesg.boot</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">…</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">bge0: &lt;Broadcom BCM57765 B0…</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">…</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># In my case: I have the “bge0"</span></div><div>--------------------------------</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">How to setup the Static IP</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># Edit  "</span><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146); font-weight: bold;">/etc/rc.conf</span><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);">” and add the lines:</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);">ifconfig_bge0</span>="inet 192.168.100.220 netmask 255.255.255.0"</div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);">defaultrouter</span>=“192.168.100.1"</div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># Edit "/etc/resolv.conf” and add the line</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);">nameserver </span>192.168.100.1</div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="color: rgb(146, 146, 146);"># To start, restart or stop the network: </span></div><div>=&gt;<span style="font-weight: bold;"> sudo</span> <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">/etc/rc.d/</span><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">netif</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 144, 81);"> start </span>|<span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);"> stop</span> | <span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);">restart</span></div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">To see the list of "Up/Down" interfaces:</span></div><div>=&gt; ifconfig -u  </div><div><br /></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">To update the "Routing" table:</span></div><div>=&gt; /etc/rc.d/routing restart</div><div><br /></div><div><font color="#929292"># The Network Tools in FreeBSD</font></div><div>/usr/ports/net-mgmt/wifimgr</div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div></en-note>